  "body": "When using a remote VC, there is a possible situation where the BN is restarted and a validator is proposing a block after restarting. \n\nThe issue is that the remote VC is sending validator registrations (mev-boost) and proposer preparer information (fee recipient) every epoch and the BN is caching that information locally which is lost upon restarts. So there is the possibility that after restart, the BN does not have that information for some time (worst case scenario whole epoch). We should look into ways to mitigate this.",
